article_title: Grocer Russ Raybould, of Russ's Market fame, dies at 92

og.description: Russ Raybould, a longtime grocer and leader in the independent grocery business, died Saturday at age 92. The Lincoln-based company he founded, B&R Stores, employs more than 2,000 people, about half of whom are part owners in the company.
